result.name: Chung So Dessert

reviews.text: This is the original Chung So, which opened in 2004. Since then, 4 outlets have opened elsewhere. It actually expanded a little here inside the mall couple years ago. It’s more spacious now, but it can still be very crowded on the weekend, including Friday night. They have been able to maintain quality and at the same time be creative with new invention.
Overall quality of the desserts here is very good.

Only know this renowned  shop in 2015, finally have chance to try at non peak hour. It designed its own dessert a little different from competitors, and it truly excites me, plus its approachable price!! No wonder why it always queue up in crowd! But I definitely will come and enjoy in afternoon.
Walnut with sesame soup is too sweet. Durian with crystal seeds is great. However, the service is not so good, the staff refuse to give out the password of the WiFi.
Very mediocre desserts with an above average price. The overly-crowded setting and next to nonexistent service were not too exciting either.

reviews.text: They have both traditional and modern desserts, quick service and I haven't been disappointed at any dessert I've chosen. I personally love their sorbets and black sesame.
Don't come here often. It will make you fat and poor at the same time. Desserts are pretty small making you wanting more. Prices are also pretty high. Having a movie star as sponsor sure helps.

Located in the heartland of HK. Here you will find mostly local enjoy a good bowl of dessert. Offering both hot and cold selection of goody foody sweet soup to warm your hearts and cool your soul.  Always pack with folks around the estate. Open till late like 1230. Authentic HK style of "sweet water" as they call it.

Delightly desert shop with a wide variety of hot and cold deserts.  In my opinion this desert shop serves the best deserts in Hong Kong.  Very popular with the locals.  Must try the durian and mango pancakes.
Truly delicious dessert for late night enjoyment.
